1
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:26,000
Dembaş temaşevanên me yê hêja, temaşevanên me yê ezîz.
 
Hello our precious viewers, our dear viewers.

2
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Ji Qenala Hatim Ji Efrînê, hezar û dused silav li we hemûyan
bin.
 
From the Hatim Ji Efrînê channel, twelve hundred greetings
to all of you.

3
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:33,000
Wek hûn dibînin em di gundê Maratê da ne.
 
As you can see, we are in the village of Maratê.

4
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:36,000
Em ê derbasî gundê Maratê bin, em ê kekekî şiyar bin.
 
We will enter the village of Maratê, we will visit a brother
who is awake (Şiyar).

5
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:40,000
Bi hevre em ê kekekî şiyar nas bikin, kesê ku wî nas nake.
 
Together we will get to know brother Şiyar, for those who do
not know him.

6
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:43,000
Kekê Şiyar di bazara Efrînê da wî ew tiştên turas li ba gund
da heye.
 
Brother Şiyar, in the market of Afrin, he has those heritage
items with him in the village.

7
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:47,000
Di xeleka gundê Birîmce da, ew dawetî e, jixwe me ra hazir
kiribû.
 
In the episode of the village of Berîmce, he was invited,
and he had prepared for us.

8
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:50,000
Û bi me ra pirr ecêb bû, min jê re got, inşallah rojekî ez ê
derbasî cem te bibim.
 
And it was very amazing to us, I told him, hopefully one day
I will visit you.

9
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:55,000
Em ê wan tiştên kevnar bibînin, em ê tiştê kevnar nas bikin,
em ê silavê xwe bigihînin te, em ê sipasiya xwe bigihînin
te.
 
We will see these old things, we will show the old things,
we will send our greetings to you, we will send our thanks
to you.

10
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:58,000
Ji ber ku wek wî got her kesî ra kekê Şiyar xwe radest dike,
ne bi sînor e.
 
Because as he said Brother Şiyar presents himself to
everyone, it is not limited.

11
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:03,000
Îro jî me xwest em derbasî cem kekê Şiyar bibin, me telefonî
wî kir, wî got mal mala we ye derbas bin.
 
Today we also wanted to visit brother Şiyar, we called him,
he said the house is your house come in.

12
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:05,000
Naha jî em ê derbasî gundê Maratê bibin.
 
And now we will enter the village of Maratê.

13
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:09,000
Em ê derbasî gundê Maratê bibin, em ê piştî wê derbasî cem
kekê Şiyar bibin.
 
We will enter the village of Maratê, after that we will
visit brother Şiyar.

14
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:14,000
Em ê silavan bigihînin te, em ê li wan tiştên turasî yê wî
kom kiriye li ba xwe mêze bikin.
 
We will send greetings to you, we will look at those
heritage items he has collected with him.

15
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:16,000
Wan tiştên bav û kala ew pê ehtîfaz kiriye.
 
Those items of the ancestors that he has preserved.

16
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:21,000
Naha jî bi me re bin, em ê derbasî gundê Maratê bibin û bîr
mekin Qenala Hatim Ji Efrînê mezin bikin.
 
And now stay with us, we will enter the village of Maratê
and don't forget to grow the Hatim Ji Efrînê channel.

17
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:24,000
Hêvîdar im em ê inşallah bibin 50,000 abone.
 
I am hopeful that we will hopefully reach 50,000
subscribers.

18
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:44,000
Naha jî bi me re bin, em biçin em bibin mêvanên gundê
Maratê, em derbasî gundê Maratê bibin.
 
And now stay with us, let's go, let's be guests of the
village of Maratê, let's enter the village of Maratê.

19
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:02,000
Zeytûnê lê zeytûnê, çi şêrîn kirî Efrînê.
 
Olive oh olive, how sweet you made Afrin.

20
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:08,000
Zeytûnê lê zeytûnê, çi şêrîn kirî Efrînê.
 
Olive oh olive, how sweet you made Afrin.

21
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:13,000
Teletat e min heşîn e, zivistan û havîn e.
 
You are green for me, winter and summer.

22
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:22,000
Teletat e min heşîn e, zivistan û havîn e.
 
You are green for me, winter and summer.

23
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:27,000
Naha jî belê temaşevanên me yê hêja, wek hûn dibînin em
derbasî gundê Maratê bûn.
 
And now yes our precious viewers, as you can see we entered
the village of Maratê.

24
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:32,000
Maşallah tebîetek vê gundê heye, mirov re cinnet e.
 
Mashallah, this village has a nature, it is a paradise for a
person.

25
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:35,000
Bihara vî gundî pirr xweş e. Naha em ê derbasî malbatekê
bin.
 
The spring of this village is very beautiful. Now we will
visit a family.

26
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:40,000
Vê malbatê mirov 50 salî 100 salî diftilîne berê zamane da.
 
This family takes a person back 50 to 100 years into the
past.

27
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:43,000
Bêhna bav û kala ji vê malê tê.
 
The scent of the ancestors comes from this house.

28
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:47,000
Û wek hûn dibînin maşallah çîçek û zeytûn û erdê wek paqij
e.
 
And as you can see, mashallah, the flowers and olives and
the ground are so clean.

29
00:02:47,000 --> 00:03:07,000
Em ê bibêjin bi sime xêrê be, li ser me û li ser milletê
me... tevdîrê wî ye.
 
We will go, may it be a good greeting, upon us and upon our
nation... it is his arrangement.

30
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:59,000
Te, te, te, te.
 
Here, here, here, here.

31
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:02,000
Elî xwarin bîne kê bixwe Elî.
 
Ali, bring food so they can eat, Ali.

32
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:12,000
Te, te, te, te.
 
Here, here, here, here.

33
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:21,000
Te, te, te, te.
 
Here, here, here, here.

34
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:23,000
Çi qewimî ye?
 
What happened?

35
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:27,000
Bi revîn.
 
They ran away.

36
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Girse riya Elî re dê.
 
Throw it in Ali's way.

37
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:41,000
Te, te, te.
 
Here, here, here.

38
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:47,000
Te, te, te, te, te, te.
 
Here, here, here, here, here, here.

39
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:50,000
Te, te, te, te.
 
Here, here, here, here.

40
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:52,000
Te ji Elî hez kirin.
 
You loved Ali.

41
00:04:52,000 --> 00:05:02,000
Te, te, te, te, te.
 
Here, here, here, here, here.

42
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:10,000
Te, te, te, te, te.
 
Here, here, here, here, here.

43
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:30,000
Te, te, te, te, te, te.
 
Here, here, here, here, here, here.

44
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:35,000
Ev e çi ye? Ev e çi ye difire?
 
What is this? What is this flying?

45
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:38,000
Ev e dîk e.
 
This is a rooster.

46
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:41,000
Dîk. Dîkekî din ji vî mezintir e nîne?
 
A rooster. Is there another rooster bigger than this?

47
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:43,000
Na na, ev çûk in, ev çûkê darê ne.
 
No no, these are birds, these are tree birds.

48
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:45,000
Ev du qiş kirin e.
 
These two fought.

49
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:52,000
Ew hatin.
 
They came.

50
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:55,000
Te, te, te.
 
Here, here, here.

51
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:58,000
Te, te, te, te.
 
Here, here, here, here.

52
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:01,000
Kekê Şiyar saatên te xweş.
 
Brother Şiyar, may your hours be good.

53
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:05,000
Xweştir azîzê min. Bixêr hatî ser çavan.
 
Yours too, my dear. Welcome, upon my eyes.

54
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:08,000
Berî her tiştî em sipasiya te dikin te qehwê xwe ji me re
vekir, em rûyê mêvandariya te hatin.
 
First of all, we thank you for opening your door for us, we
came for your hospitality.

55
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:12,000
Wellehî em pirr kêfxweş bûn. Maşallah hewşa te cinet e.
 
By God we were very happy. Mashallah your yard is a
paradise.

56
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:17,000
Ser çavan. Çawa dixwazin werin mal mala we ye.
 
Upon my eyes. Whenever you want to come, the house is your
house.

57
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:20,000
Xwedê te razî be, em qet tu wext da te nabînin...
 
May God be pleased with you, we never see you anytime...

58
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:25,000
Welleh rûmet e. Rûmet. Silav ji te re mamoste Xelîl.
 
By God it is an honor. An honor. Greetings to you teacher
Xelîl.

59
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:28,000
Em sipasiya te dikin Kekê Şiyar. Wek mamoste Xelîl gotiye...
 
We thank you Brother Şiyar. As teacher Xelîl has said...

60
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:31,000
Em dê bên saatên xweş, te qehwê xwe ji me re vekir.
 
We will come with good hours, you opened your door to us.

61
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:35,000
Ser çavan, hûn bixêr hatin.
 
Upon my eyes, you are welcome.

62
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:38,000
Em dixwazin tu ji me re bêje, ji kîjan wext da te dest bi vî
malê kir?
 
We want you to tell us, since what time did you start this
house (collection)?

63
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:42,000
Welle malê xwe bi xwe teqrîben... min 10 sal heta 15 salan
e...
 
Well, the house itself approximately... I have been for 10
to 15 years...

64
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:47,000
Teqrîben 10 hezar heta 15 hezar heb e. Heta min dest pê kir
ev tiştî min hilanî ye.
 
Approximately 10 thousand to 15 thousand items. Since I
started I have kept this thing.

65
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:51,000
Me hilanî ye da em li van tiştan miqate bin, eva turasê me
ye, em naxwazin turasê me winda bibe.
 
We kept it so we can take care of these things, this is our
heritage, we do not want our heritage to be lost.

66
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:57,000
Em dixwazin tim û tim pêşkeşî xelkê bikin ma daku bizanin,
wate çawa bav û kalên xwedê dijiyan.
 
We want to always present it to the people so they know,
meaning how the ancestors of God lived.

67
00:06:57,000 --> 00:07:01,000
Karê berê çawa bû, dema ku diçûn gund, car caran diçûne nav
zeviyan...
 
How the work of the past was, when they went to the village,
sometimes they went into the fields...

68
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:07,000
Sibehî saet pêncan derdiketin, ji xew radibûn... pel û nîr
didanîn milê xwe...
 
In the morning at five o'clock they went out, woke up from
sleep... put the leaves and yokes on their shoulders...

69
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:11,000
Dêlikê xwe radibûn, diçûn nav zeviyan nav dexl û derê...
 
They picked up their hoes, went into the fields among the
crops...

70
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:14,000
Ew palê diçûn nav dexl û zeviyan.
 
Those reapers went into the crops and fields.

71
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:19,000
Lê min dît ev tişt pir kar dikir, min a ta quweta xwe ez
hilanî.
 
But I saw this thing was working a lot, I saved it to my
strength.

72
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:23,000
Û ava ez ev tiştî wate weke em miqate bikin, qeçikên me ew
qeçikên me dibînin...
 
And so I mean for us to preserve this thing, our children
those children of ours see it...

73
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:27,000
Teqrîben niha 1300 perçe cem me hene.
 
Approximately now we have 1300 pieces.

74
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:33,000
1300 perçe tiştên turasî, van tiştan gişkan kevnar ne.
 
1300 pieces of heritage items, all these things are old.

75
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:38,000
Pir tişt em hene Kekê Şiyar, lê em van tiştan kêmtir dibînin
em zêde dikin.
 
We have many things Brother Şiyar, but we see less of these
things so we add.

76
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:42,000
Wate pir tişt em hene kêmasî nîne...
 
Meaning we have many things there is no shortage...

77
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:49,000
Na na, gelek in tiştên me, tiştên weke menzil em dibînin...
 
No no, our things are many, things like the house we see...

78
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:54,000
Yek e, tiştên sifir e... dû re radyo ye berê, televizyonê
berê hene.
 
One is, copper things... then there is the old radio, the
old television.

79
00:07:54,000 --> 00:08:00,000
Em dibînin menzilî jî ewatê menzilî jî e, yê ziraetê mesela
nîr, cencer heye, şixre heye.
 
We see house items too, agricultural ones for example yoke,
threshing sled, sickle.

80
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:08,000
Kêf heye, pallo ye, fîşekê dêw e, nav heye giş tiştên pir
kevn in.
 
There is a hoe, a reaper, a giant cartridge, there are
names, they are all very old things.

81
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:12,000
Û yên malan menzilî jî tiştên baqirî, yên berê.
 
And for the houses too, the copper things, of the past.

82
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:16,000
Sahan in, kevçî ne, text in... Berî yên sifir.
 
They are plates, spoons, wood... Before the copper ones.

83
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:21,000
Dû re sifir derket in... evna giş... destar, du cure destar
heye.
 
Then copper ones came out... all these... handmill, there
are two types of handmills.

84
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:26,000
Destarek e yê genim dikişîne... destarê din firîk pê
dikişînin.
 
One is a handmill that grinds wheat... the other handmill
they grind frik with it.

85
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:30,000
Wate evna giş me miqate kirine... Heta em dikarin em tişt em
dibînin...
 
Meaning we have preserved all these... As much as we can,
things we see...

86
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:32,000
Lê wekî tu dizanî...
 
But as you know...

87
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:35,000
Lê cem te zêde bû ye wek vana cihek heye?
 
But it has increased for you, is there a place like these?

88
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:41,000
Wekî vana ez dibêjim em naxwazin zêde bikin... tiştan ez
dibînim em dikirin...
 
Like these I say we don't want to increase... things I see
we buy...

89
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:45,000
Û mesele tu dibînî hewce bike tu dîsa amade dikî?
 
And for example you see if it's necessary you prepare it
again?

90
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:52,000
Erê... wisa ew roj em li kû dibînin... meselen tiştên ku cem
me zêde be em didin hinan.
 
Yes... like that day where we see... for example things that
we have extra we give to others.

91
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:58,000
Da hinek jî hebe, ma qet ev tişt winda nebe.
 
So others can have some too, so this thing never gets lost.

92
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:03,000
Û wek dî jî tiştê ji bo dîk û mirîşkê te, û pezê te...
 
And also the things for your rooster and chicken, and your
sheep...

93
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:07,000
Gelek sîtilên baqir, beroşên baqir, leganên baqir...
 
Many copper buckets, copper pots, copper basins...

94
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:11,000
Heta tepsiyên baqir ji van mezinên wan cem me hene...
 
Even copper trays from those large ones we have with us...

95
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:17,000
Çenteyên berê, tenekeyên berê cihêza wan wek digotin.
 
Old bags, old tin containers, their dowry as they used to
say.

96
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:23,000
Sandoq... ew gelek in cem me. Qenewîç tiştên han e, sîtil...
fîşek.
 
Trunks... there are many with us. Embroidery things are
here, bucket... cartridge.

97
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:28,000
Evna hemû, luks e hene, heta paporê spêrto heye cem me.
 
These all, there are pressure lamps, even spirit stoves we
have with us.

98
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:30,000
Heta em dikarin em tişt dibînin em dikirin.
 
As much as we can we see things and we buy them.

99
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:34,000
Û te ev tiştan jî li hewşê belav kiriye, maşallah em
dibînin.
 
And you have spread these things in the yard too, mashallah
we see.

100
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:37,000
Hewşa min em birin sê qisman e.
 
We divided my yard into three sections.

101
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:40,000
Qismek jê ev tiştê kevnar e.
 
One section of it is these old things.

102
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

103
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:43,000
Ê diduyan jî heywanat hene.
 
The second one is animals.

104
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:47,000
Ê sêyem çandinî ne... çandinî şitil, gul û kulîlk e.
 
The third is agriculture... agriculture seedlings, roses and
flowers.

105
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:51,000
Çîçek ta pir hewandin maşallah, heywan jî...
 
You nurtured flowers very much mashallah, animals too...

106
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:57,000
Heywan jî hene qumrî ne, tawiz in, mirîşk in, haşok in dêlik
û kûçik in.
 
Animals are there too, there are doves, peacocks, chickens,
puppies, dogs and hounds.

107
00:09:57,000 --> 00:10:00,000
Ya gundî tişta di gund de çêdibe em dihewînin.
 
Whatever belongs to the village, what happens in the village
we nurture.

108
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:04,000
Em dixwazin meselen noka, daxwaz û dawetek ma, daxwaz ji te
kirin li Efrînê?
 
We want to ask, for example now, if there is a request or a
wedding, did they request you in Afrin?

109
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,000
Em hazir dibin.
 
We get ready.

110
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:08,000
Ma te me'ared û faliyet dikirin?
 
Did you do exhibitions and activities?

111
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:16,000
Me'ared me pirr faliyet kirin. Wekî tu bibê... Staz
Evdirehman jî tevlî Efrîn... me yek awil.. yek li wî alî
kirin... li şehran de meselen. Yanî kel û pelê me... me...
li seeta xwe şanî wan da.
 
Exhibitions, we did a lot of activities. Like you could
say... Mr. Abdulrahman also regarding Afrin... we did one
first... one on that side... in the cities, for example.
Meaning our equipment and items... we... we exhibited them
at our own times.

112
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:29,000
Û li her faliyetekê jî, ku em te dibînin, tu yek bi yek
tiştên xwe tînî, bi makîneyên xwe tu hazir dibî... û te
lîstin e... naha meselen wek carê çûyî, me'redek di wê de tu
hazir bûyî... ê turas.
 
And in every activity, as we see you, you bring your things
one by one, you get ready with your machines... and you
play... now for example like last time, there was an
exhibition in which you were present... of heritage.

113
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:30,000
Turas, erê.
 
Heritage, yes.

114
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:32,000
Ew tiştî pirr in te... meselen em...
 
Those things are many with you... for example we...

115
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:34,000
Ê.. mûzîk. Ê mûzîka efrîn.. e l'wê jî hazir bûn...
 
Yes.. music. Yes, Afrin's music.. yes, we were ready there
too...

116
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:54,000
Belê, tu l'wê jî hazir bî. Meselen, xelekeke din da yê
l'gundî.. bernamêk.. tu l'wê jî hazir bî. Te tiştên xwe
turas, naha ev tiştên ku em dibê.. malan da nêyî dîtin. Bes
l'ba te hene, yanî dema... te.. da'wet yan te.. dawetek yan
fealiyetek hebe.. wek turasî yê berê, l'her daxwazîyekê yan
tu amade dikiye... amade dikin?
 
Yes, you were ready there too. For example, in another
episode in the village.. a program.. you were ready there
too. You brought your heritage items, now these things that
we speak of.. are not seen in homes anymore. They are only
with you, meaning when... you.. a wedding or you.. if there
is a wedding or an activity.. like the old heritage, do you
prepare it for every request... do you prepare?

117
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:55,000
Em hazir dibin, derdikevin.
 
We get ready, we go out.

118
00:10:55,000 --> 00:11:00,000
Ez zanim mimkin, daxwaz û fealiyet û dawetan li mentîqê de..
tu l' çend dawetan derketî tu?
 
I know it is possible, requests and activities and weddings
in the region.. how many weddings have you gone out to?

119
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:04,000
